# Retail-Sales-Analytics-Dashboard-Web-App

Retail Sales Analytics Dashboard & Web App

Python · SQL · Pandas · Streamlit · Power BI · Tableau

An end-to-end retail analytics solution that turns raw transactional data into actionable business insights — combining a Power BI/Tableau reporting layer with a companion self-serve Streamlit web app.

🔗 Repo: Retail-Sales-Analytics-Dashboard


Overview

Retail businesses generate large volumes of transactional data daily. Without proper analysis, valuable insights regarding sales growth, customer preferences, and product performance remain hidden.

This project analyzes 9,994 retail transactions across 21 columns to surface revenue trends, top-performing segments, and regional/customer behavior — then makes those insights accessible two ways:

Power BI / Tableau dashboards for stakeholders who want polished, presentation-ready reporting.
A Streamlit web app for stakeholders who want self-serve, filterable access without needing a BI tool license.

Highlights

Analyzed 9,994 retail transactions across 21 columns to uncover revenue trends and top-performing segments, extracting KPIs with Pandas and SQL.
Designed Power BI dashboards tracking 10+ KPIs with cards, dynamic charts, maps, and slicers for self-serve analysis; recreated key visuals in Tableau for executive presentations.
Built a companion interactive Streamlit app exposing the same KPIs via dynamic filters, giving stakeholders self-serve access without a BI tool license.
Exported structured results into multi-sheet Excel workbooks via openpyxl; automated delivery, saving ~5 hours/week for stakeholders

